article.headline: Wagner 69, Albany 59
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Courtney Pritchard had 18 points, 15 in the second half, and eight rebounds to lead Wagner's rally over Albany 69-59 Tuesday night. Wagner, which trailed by 36-24 at the break, was still behind 45-35 with 15:10 left when the Seahawks scored 15 of the next 19 points for a 50-49 lead. Pritchard capped the run with a steal and layup. The Great Danes (2-7) briefly regained the lead when Aquawasi St. Hillaire hit a 17-foot baseline jumper to make it 51-50. But the Seahawks pulled ahead for good by scoring nine unanswered points with 4:41 to play. Nigel Wyatte scored 11 points for Wagner (3-6), which held Albany to 29-percent shooting in the second half. Sean Munson added 10 points for the Seahawks and DeEarnest McLemore nine. Sophomore Levi Levine led Albany with 15 points and eight rebounds, and Aquawasi St. Hillaire had 13 points and freshman Jon Iati 12.
